ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
******
[2] Germany
Date: Fri 5 Oct 2007
Source: Friedrich-Loeffler-Institut (FLI) website [in German, trans. &
abbreviated by communicator, edited]
<http://www.fli.bund.de/253.html?&no_cache=1&tx_ttnews[tt_news]=297&cHash=0111265f06>

As of 5 Oct 2007, 12 323 cases of bluetongue disease have been confirmed in
Germany.
It is not clear whether this number refers to individual animals or
holdings affected with multiple cases. It is likely a combination of the
above and due to a lack of data it is not possible to establish within
herd/flock incidence and mortality rates. In some parts of Germany only one
animal per holding is blood sampled to establish the presence of the virus,
additional suspects from the same farm are confirmed on clinical diagnosis
only.
For a BTV distribution map in Germany, see
<http://www.fli.bund.de:80/uploads/media/FLI_BTV8_051007.jpg>.
